# AgenticAI Java conventions

## Stack

Spring Boot 3.3 + Java 17 + JPA + Maven. Source: `backend/src/main/java/com/aidecision/agentic/`.

## Package layout

| Package | Responsibility |
|---------|----------------|
| `orchestrator/` | Workflow planner, DAG validation, executor, compound expansion |
| `service/` | Business logic, async chat, run assembly |
| `tool/` + `tool/impl/` | Registered tools and HTTP/LLM invocations |
| `controller/` | REST endpoints (thin — delegate to services) |
| `dto/` | Request/response records for the API |
| `entity/` + `repository/` | JPA persistence |

## Style

- Prefer package-private or public methods with clear names; `methodName_scenario` in tests.
- DTOs use validation annotations (`@NotBlank`, `@Valid`) at controller boundaries.
- Keep controllers thin; orchestration and SQL/LLM work stay in services/tools.
- No secrets in code — use `backend/.env` (gitignored) and Spring `@ConfigurationProperties`.

## Orchestration rules

- Workflow planner output must pass `WorkflowDagValidator` before execution.
- Tools are registered in DB (`orchestrator_tool`); executor resolves by `tool_name`.
- Async runs persist step status for polling; failures must update run state.
- Do not call live Azure OpenAI or SQL Server in unit tests — use mocks/stubs.

## Tests (required for new behavior)

- Mirror package: `backend/src/test/java/.../<ClassName>Test.java`.
- JUnit 5 + AssertJ + Mockito; avoid `@SpringBootTest` unless integration is required.
- Run: `cd backend && mvn -q test -Dtest=<ClassName>Test`.
